 an intermediate exploration variance of σ =2.5 achieves\nthebestoverallbalance,whilealargervarianceslightlyimprovesLast-1accuracy\nat the cost of weaker overall alignment.\n\n=== PAGE 24 ===\nAdapting Omni-LLM as a Reference-Free AV Sync Evaluator 3\nTable 10: Complete reward ablation aligned with the pairwise, listwise, and dual-\nreward comparison in the main paper. We report the full metric suite together with\nrelative changes against the PFT baseline.\nReward NDCG MRR Kendall Spearman Top-1ACC PairACC LastACC\nPFT-baseline 0.9353 0.7316 0.4515 0.5366 55.80 71.16 53.8\nPairReward 0.9396 0.7584 0.4700 0.5560 60.00 71.70 56.4\n(+0.5%) (+3.7%) (+4.1%) (+3.6%) (+7.5%) (+0.8%) (+4.8%)\nListReward 0.9339 0.7371 0.4267 0.5122 55.6 70.34 44.0\n(-0.2%) (+0.8%) (-5.5%) (-4.5%) (-0.4%) (-1.2%) (-18.2%)\nDualRewards0.9435 (+0.9%)0.7674 (+4.9%)0.4899 (+8.5%)0.5837 (+8.8%)61.4 (+10.0%)72.38 (+1.7%)55.0 (+2.2%)\nTable11:CompleteablationontheGaussianexplorationstandarddeviation(σ)used\nduring RL post-training. The intermediate setting σ = 2.5 gives the strongest overall\ntrade-off, while σ=10.0 yields the best Last ACC.\nσ NDCG MRR Kendall Spearman Top-1 ACC Pair ACC Last ACC\n2.0 0.9366 0.7327 0.4625 0.5493 56.20 71.56 54.00\n2.5 0.9435 0.7674 0.4899 0.5837 61.40 72.38 55.0\n10.0 0.9405 0.7503 0.4768 0.5673 58.60 71.70 55.60\nA.4 Global Reward and Metric Formulations\nEvaluation Metrics. For each visual anchor x, let Y ={y ,...,y } denote the\nx 1 K\ncandidate audio-video pairs, with predicted scores ˆs=[sˆ ,...,sˆ ] and ground-\n1 K\ntruth scores g=[g ,...,g ]. The predicted ranking is obtained by sorting can-\n1 K\ndidates in descending order of ˆs, while the ground-truth ranking is induced by\ndescendingorderofg.Allrankingmetricsarecomputedfromtheseorderedlists.\nPairwise Accuracy. Given a valid pair (i,j) with g ̸= g , PairAcc evaluates\ni j\nwhether the predicted ordering agrees with the ground-truth ordering:\n1 (cid:88)\nPairAcc= I[(sˆ >sˆ )⇔(g >g )],\n|P| i j i j\n(i,